Un poco más cerca y te muerde >:-)

http://wiki.debian.org/Thunar

***
Installation

If you are running Xfce, Thunar is already installed. If you already have 
Gnome installed, you could just install the thunar package. However, if 
you are using a more minimal X11 setup, for example, with only a window 
manager like Openbox, you should also install the gnome-icon-theme 
package. Most other icon themes, such as the tango-icon-theme, inherit 
some icons from the gnome theme. Thunar is pretty useless without icons. 
***

Si tienes algún problema al instalarlo y/o configurarlo como 
predeterminado explica qué es lo que has hecho y qué te sucede 
_exactamente_.

Saludos,

